cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.DM, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the problem of extending data mining approaches to cases where data points arise in the form of individual graphs. This topic falls under the sub-category of "Structural Analysis in Networks" (cs.SI) as well as "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) since the paper explores practical solutions for finding low-dimensionality in ensembles of graphs. The paper also discusses the challenge of defining a suitable pairwise similarity metric in the space of graphs, which is a common problem in "Data Mining" (cs.DM) and "Statistical Learning" (cs.SD). Finally, the paper incorporates these approaches with equation-free techniques to enhance scientific computation of network evolution dynamics, which falls under the sub-category of "Networks and Evolution" (cs.NE).
